Compartir es bueno
Y cortés. Lo dice Bruce Schneier en <a href="http://news.com.com/2100-1029_3-6088741.html">Does Wi-Fi security matter?</a>.


<blockquote>
"I have a completely open Wi-Fi network," Schneier told ZDNet UK. "Firstly, I don't care if my neighbors are using my network. Secondly, I've protected my computers. Thirdly, it's polite. When people come over they can use it."
</blockquote>

Visto en <a href="http://www.schneier.com/blog/archives/2006/06/schneier_asks_t.html">Schneier Asks to Be Hacked</a>.  


